article.headline: Princeton 54, Dartmouth 38
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Ian Hummer scored 11 points for Princeton and was one of only three players to score in double figures for either team, leading the Tigers in a 54-38 win over Dartmouth on Saturday night. Dan Mavraides added 10 points as the only other Princeton player in double digits. The Tigers (13-5, 4-0 Ivy League) stretched their winning streak to six games, solidifying second place in the conference behind the conference's other undefeated team -- Cornell. The teams traded leads in the opening half, and the Big Green took a 21-19 advantage into the break. But Douglas Davis hit a 3-pointer in the first minute of the second half, sparking a 12-3 Princeton run for a seven-point lead less than 6 minutes into the frame. The Tigers never trailed again. Robby Pride was the only Dartmouth player in double figures, scoring 10. Dartmouth (4-16, 0-6) has lost five straight.
